 that had a break for a month because I was in Hong Kong. 

00:00:09.760 --> 00:00:14.740
 Today's episode was suggested by ... me, because I saw this tip on tumblr and I found it 

00:00:14.740 --> 00:00:19.509
 that it was very cool and I wanted to copy it and I also wanted to choose something 

00:00:19.509 --> 00:00:23.380
 that is fairly easy to get back in the mood of Make Thrift Buy. 

00:00:23.380 --> 00:00:28.130
 What I wanted to copy was this daisy-breasted cropped t-shirt. The daisies have too 

00:00:28.130 --> 00:00:32.029
 creepy little smiles on their face. So let's get started. 

00:00:32.029 --> 00:00:37.300
 I have this half-cut shirt that I originally bought second hand and used for fabric 

00:00:37.300 --> 00:00:41.649
 in episode 10. I didn't want to throw it away at the end of episode 10, 

00:00:41.649 --> 00:00:44.410
 and I'm glad I didn't because I can now use it for this episode. 

00:00:44.410 --> 00:00:49.039
 First of all it seemed like a good idea to make the sleeves a bit more, well ... right. 

00:00:49.040 --> 00:00:51.980
 So I cut off the other sleeve so that it matched the first. 

00:00:51.989 --> 00:00:56.890
 This shirt has already been cut off. Nevertheless, if you come with a new one 

00:00:56.890 --> 00:01:00.260
 shirt works, all you have to do is cut the bottom of the shirt to a length that 

00:01:00.260 --> 00:01:04.470
 fits you, but add a few inches for hemming before you cut it. 

00:01:04.470 --> 00:01:11.470
 With the shirt inside out, I folded the sleeve once and then twice. 

00:01:15.020 --> 00:01:17.140
 Then I selected a stitch for stretchy fabric 

00:01:18.600 --> 00:01:21.520
 and I sewed around the entire sleeve in this way. 

00:01:26.740 --> 00:01:32.380
 When both sleeves were finished and the shirt was still inside out, I hemmed the bottom of the shirt. 

00:01:32.380 --> 00:01:36.290
 I only folded the bottom edge once because I didn't have too much fabric left to work with, 

00:01:36.290 --> 00:01:40.630
 and as I did with the sleeves, I sewed around the entire hem with a zigzag stitch. 

00:01:40.630 --> 00:01:46.049
 A smart way to ensure that the hem does not bend is to sew a piece of paper 

00:01:46.049 --> 00:01:50.670
 on the shirt when you sew on the hem. An even better way is to put it under 

00:01:50.670 --> 00:01:55.299
 place the shirt when you sew so that you can still see what you are doing. 

00:01:55.299 --> 00:02:00.329
 Then I just tore away the paper and ... spent ten minutes removing the little papers 

00:02:00.329 --> 00:02:06.619
 between the stitches, and I'm done! I have a crop top. 

00:02:06.619 --> 00:02:10.479
 Now it's time to add the daisies. I have drawn two daisies 

00:02:10.479 --> 00:02:14.700
 using Photoshop, but it's such a simple design that you could do this on yourself 

00:02:14.700 --> 00:02:20.349
 MS Paint. I made two and then printed on ironing paper and me 

00:02:20.349 --> 00:02:25.090
 she cut out. Then I put on my new crop top and decided where I wanted the daisies 

00:02:25.090 --> 00:02:29.790
 and I stuck a small amount of blu-tack where I wanted the middle of each daisy 

00:02:29.790 --> 00:02:35.040
 because you don't see your pencil on a black fabric, I won't wind my chalk. Then took it 

00:02:35.040 --> 00:02:42.040
 I took the pictures off their paper and I put them on the shirt. 

00:02:42.040 --> 00:02:45.120
 [music] 

